(2197, 913, 'skrocony_opis', 'MDC2  – a developer of sustainable warehouse and industrial space operating on the Polish market, has reached an agreement with Fortress REIT Limited – South Africa’s largest owner and developer of core, premium-grade logistics real estate. '),
(2198, 913, '_skrocony_opis', 'field_6144f5f47a09c'),
(2199, 913, 'opis', '<strong>January 18, 2022, Warsaw: </strong><strong>MDC<sup>2</sup> <sup> </sup>– a developer of sustainable warehouse and industrial space operating on the Polish market, has reached an agreement with Fortress REIT Limited – South Africa’s largest owner and developer of core, premium-grade logistics real estate. </strong>\r\n\r\nMDC<sup>2</sup> Park Łódź South, located in Central Poland, announced its first collaborative project with Fortress REIT Limited today. This will be MDC<sup>2 </sup>’s third logistics development and Fortress REIT’s third logistic park in Poland.\r\n\r\nMDC<sup>2 </sup>Park Łódź South is designed with ESG at its core and MDC<sup>2</sup> <sup> </sup>will certify the project to BREEAM New Construction Excellent. ESG is a cornerstone of MDC<sup>2</sup>‘s strategy – all buildings developed by the company are to meet the best practices and requirements of sustainable construction, i.e. 95% of construction materials per project are recyclable and roofs of its buildings are designed to be PV ready.\r\n\r\nMDC<sup>2 </sup>Park Łódź South, to be developed by MDC<sup>2</sup> and announced in September 2021, will accommodate a distribution centre located in Central Poland south of Łódź, at the junction of the A1 motorway and the National Roads no. 91 and 12. The project offers a leasable area up to 80,000 m<sup>2</sup> of modern, environmentally sustainable logistics space, the completion of which is planned for Q3 2023.\r\n\r\n“We are extremely happy to have acquired this project as it perfectly fits Fortress REIT Limited strategic investment profile. MDC<sup>2</sup> Park Łódź South shall not only provide the highest standard of modern big-box logistic facility, but will also contain solutions addressing environmental responsibility as well as sustainable building features sought for by the tenant.” – stated <strong>Maciej Tuszyński</strong>, <strong>Managing Director Europe at Fortress REIT Limited.</strong> – “The Project’s strategic location and its exceptional quality planned by its developer – MDC<sup>2</sup>, coupled with financial strength and experience of Fortress REIT Limited shall undoubtedly result in the commercial success of this venture.”\r\n\r\n“Sustainable logistics and distribution parks are in demand in Poland, with more clients looking to have a robust and localised supply chain. MDC<sup>2</sup> Park Łódź South, due to its central location, is a strategic fit for Fortress REIT as it sits in the heart of Poland’s main distribution hub.” – said <strong>Hadley Dean</strong>, <strong>Founder of MDC<sup>2</sup>.</strong> – “For the next decade, the Polish logistics market will continue to outperform Western European countries in the growth of both total activity and net absorption.”\r\n\r\nThe advisors in the transaction were Savills and ARC Capital Markets.'),
