(4634, 1135, 'skrocony_opis', 'MDC2 – a developer of sustainable warehouse and industrial space operating on the Polish market – strengthens its development team by hiring Dariusz Proniewicz, the highly experienced BTS developments professional.'),
(4635, 1135, '_skrocony_opis', 'field_6144f5f47a09c'),
(4636, 1135, 'opis', 'Dariusz Proniewicz will join MDC<sup>2 </sup>in January 2023 as BTS Development Director. In his new role he will be responsible for sourcing, developing and leasing tailor-made warehouse and logistics projects for specific tenants.\r\n\r\nDariusz has over 18 years of experience in the development of industrial and logistics properties in Poland, working for Prologis, Goodman (GLP) and Panattoni among others. He transacted close to 900 000 m<sup>2 </sup>of warehouse space and acquired 300 hectares of land. Notable leasing transactions with Dariusz’s involvement include Action, Knorr-Bremse, Amazon, Intermarche, Weber, Unilever and  Raben.\r\n\r\nHe is a graduate of Kraków University of Technology and completed postgraduate studies in Real Estate Valuation at Technical University of Warsaw and Property Appraisal and Management studies at Sheffield Hallam University.\r\n\r\n“With the growing number of production companies choosing Poland for their manufacturing location, it was crucial for us to acquire the top BTS professional in the market to be able to meet requirements of our clients. We are delighted to welcome Dariusz Proniewicz to our team. His track record and work attitude are a perfect fit for MDC<sup>2 </sup>whose culture is based on the key values of Trust, Fairness and Empowerment, Balance and Fun and Freedom.” - <strong>said Maciej Madejak, </strong>Chief Development Officer, Founder of MDC<sup>2</sup>.'),
