INSERT INTO `akwp_postmeta` (`meta_id`, `post_id`, `meta_key`, `meta_value`) VALUES
(4747, 1316, 'skrocony_opis', 'Rohlig Suus anchors MDC2 Park Gliwice – forecasted to be the greenest and highest scoring warehouse project in Poland “BREEAM New Construction Outstanding”. MDC² Park Gliwice is located at the intersection of the A4 and A1 motorways in Gliwice, Upper Silesia\n\n'),
(4748, 1316, 'opis', 'Rohlig Suus Logistics have leased 20,393 m<sup>2</sup>, which will include 19,773 m<sup>2</sup> of warehouse space and 420 m<sup>2</sup> of office and social space.  The total area of the 3 warehouse buildings in the park will exceed 57,000 m<sup>2</sup>.\n\nRohlig Suus Logistics is one of the fastest-growing, market-leading logistics operators in Poland.  Rohlig Suus Logistics has been operating for over 30 years, managing logistics and supply chains on six continents.  The company employs over over 2000 employees in over 30 offices in Europe.\n\n“We have chosen MDC2 Park Gliwice because of its location and very high score in the BREEAM New Construction certification. ESG issues are extremely important in the development strategy of SUUS. We want our facilities to be \"green\", but also appropriately adapted to the needs of employees or truck drivers, which also affects the provision of the highest quality services to our customers” – explained <strong>Sylwester Wzorek, Senior Facility Manager w Rohlig Suus Logistics</strong>.\n\n“Year by year, we notice the growing development of the Silesia region, which is why we decided to lease a new, larger warehouse in MDC² Park Gliwice. The location of the facility, at the intersection of the A1 and A4 motorways, is also extremely important to us,” says <strong><em>Grzegorz Łukaszek</em>, Branch Director Katowice at Rohlig Suus Logistics</strong>. “This investment will significantly increase our operational capabilities, which will allow us to improve our services, which we direct in the region, among others, to clients from the automotive sector – he added.\n\nBoth MDC<sup>2</sup> and Rohlig Suus Logistics ensure that business strategies are implemented in accordance with the concept of sustainable development. The ESG policy in both companies is of paramount importance, taking into account environmental issues, the well-being of customers, suppliers and employees.\n\nWithin the area of the Gliwice’s project there is a Rest &amp; Move area which is an innovative concept on the Polish market, promoting a healthy lifestyle and improving working conditions for all users of the developer\'s warehouse facilities.  Benefits include a gym, delivered in partnership with \"TruckersLife\" foundation, and a multi-sport pitch, and places to rest and relax.\n\n“A social space dedicated to visitors of Rohlig Suus Logistics will be built within the leased area. This is an exception on the Polish market, which, along with the development of the ESG policy in the industry, is gaining more and more importance, especially in relation to the professional group of truck drivers. Caring for their well-being is in the interest of all stakeholders involved in logistics processes. As part of a similar concept, MDC<sup>2</sup> prepares the surroundings of the entire complex. For this purpose, a special Rest&amp;Move zone will be created including a gym - as part of the partnership with the TruckersLife foundation - a multisport pitch and places to rest. The idea behind the Rest&amp;Move is to promote a healthy lifestyle and improve working conditions for all users of the developer\'s warehouse park.” says <strong>Katarzyna Dudzik, Development Director at MDC<sup>2</sup>.</strong>\n\nMDC<sup>2</sup> Park Gliwice is being developed to BREEAM New Construction certification guidelines at the Outstanding level. Such a high rating is possible thanks to the use of a number of solutions that increase the energy efficiency of buildings, as well as thanks to a well-thought-out environment rich in biodiversity and prepared with the well-being of employees in mind.\n\nRohlig Suus will start its operations in MDC<sup>2</sup> Park Gliwice in autumn this year.\n\nThe investor of the project is a German fund whose assets are managed by Invesco Real Estate. Triflow agency and Greenberg Traurig law firm advised on the lease transaction.'),
