(4896, 1389, 'skrocony_opis', 'MDC2 attracted AFL – a global leader in optical fiber network infrastructure – to MDC2 Park Gliwice. With signing the lease agreement AFL enters Poland with its new production facility. The signing of the lease coincides with the global leader\'s debut on the Polish market. MDC2 Park Gliwice is predicted to be the most ecological and highest rated (BREEAM New Construction Outstanding) warehouse development in Poland. MDC² Park Gliwice is located in Gliwice, Upper Silesia, at the junction of two motorways - the A4 and the A1\n\n'),
(4897, 1389, 'opis', 'MDC<sup>2</sup> - a developer of sustainable warehouse and logistics space operating on the Polish market, together with an investor - Invesco Real Estate, has concluded a lease agreement with AFL.\n\nAFL is an international company providing comprehensive optical fiber network infrastructure solutions for the  service provider, hyperscale, energy, enterprise and  industrial sector.\n\n\"AFL\'s mission is to connect our customers worldwide with innovative technologies, exceptional products and high-quality services. The landlord\'s ESG policy is very important to us. We chose MDC<sup>2</sup> Park Gliwice because it uses the environmentally sustainable solutions to ensure low carbon and energy efficient operations. The park\'s location in the immediate vicinity of the A4 and A1 motorways, access to a skilled workforce and the support of the Katowice Special Economic Zone also contributed to the choice of the location,\" says Daniel Rose, Managing Director – Connectivity, EMEA, - AFL.\n\nMDC<sup>2</sup>\'s ESG strategy, which underpins the company\'s growth, is guided by its motto \"Building for Good\", according to which it builds warehouse parks for good for a sustainable future for tenants, investors, local communities, the environment and the industry as a whole.\n\n\"We welcome AFL to Poland, to the prime location of   MDC<sup>2</sup> Park Gliwice, in the belief that the global IT leader\'s market success will be seamlessly transferred to Poland,\" said Katarzyna Dudzik, Development Director,  MDC<sup>2</sup>.\n\nMDC<sup>2</sup> is committed to modern and environmentally friendly solutions. The focus is placed on adapting the roofs for the installation of photovoltaic panels.\n\nTenants will be guaranteed a system for monitoring their energy consumption. The developer has also provided charging points for electric vehicles and bicycle sheds. A rainwater retention system will also be installed. As part of the internal policy, 95% of the building materials are expected to be recyclable.\n\nMDC<sup>2</sup> Park Gliwice, which was completed in autumn 2023, comprises three warehouse buildings with a total area of 59,000 sq. m.. The logistics centre is located at the junction of two motorways: A4 and A1. The surrounding transport routes also include a network of national roads, including the local Drogowa Trasa Średnicowa - extremely popular in the Upper Silesian agglomeration.\n\nColliers consultants were involved in the AFL lease transaction.'),
